Oh, God, it's 8:00!

14:38.342 --> 14:40.243
We're supposed to meet the
gang at the bar to celebrate.

14:40.244 --> 14:41.411
Oh, God. Okay, listen.

14:41.412 --> 14:43.446
When we meet them,
we have to keep it together.

14:43.447 --> 14:44.447
Can you keep it together?!

14:44.448 --> 14:46.049
No, I can't keep it together!

14:46.050 --> 14:49.319
Robin: I have never seen you
guys looking so at peace.

14:49.320 --> 14:50.386
(Both sigh)

14:50.387 --> 14:51.454
To Lily and Marshall.

14:51.455 --> 14:52.856
Lily and Marshall.

14:52.857 --> 14:53.857
Well, thank you.

14:53.858 --> 14:56.726
I mean,
we've never been happier.

14:56.727 --> 14:58.328
(Rock music playing)
This is a nightmare!

14:58.329 --> 15:00.029
We've done everything wrong!

15:00.030 --> 15:01.498
(Screams)

15:01.499 --> 15:03.733
The iPod was on shuffle!

15:03.734 --> 15:04.801
(Rock music stops)

15:04.802 --> 15:05.835
The Jerky Boys!

15:05.836 --> 15:08.004
Our baby heard the Jerky Boys!

15:08.005 --> 15:09.506
You know what,
the Jerky Boys are funny.

15:09.507 --> 15:12.075
The Jerky Boys aren't funny,
they are awful.

15:12.076 --> 15:13.443
You know what, fine,
if you don't think

15:13.444 --> 15:15.044
the Jerky Boys are funny,
then I'm not sure

15:15.045 --> 15:16.813
that I can raise a child
with you, liver lips.

15:16.814 --> 15:18.681
(Gasps)

15:18.682 --> 15:20.250
Marshall, I don't like this.

15:20.251 --> 15:21.384
I know. Okay?

15:21.385 --> 15:23.119
I don't like it either.

15:23.120 --> 15:25.989
It's like I have a hot, burning

15:25.990 --> 15:28.725
ball of stress in my chest,

15:28.726 --> 15:30.560
and nothing
will make it go away!

15:30.561 --> 15:31.728
You're not pregnant.

15:31.729 --> 15:33.563
Well, that did it.

15:33.564 --> 15:36.766
I know this probably comes
as quite a disappointment.

15:38.269 --> 15:39.802
Yeah.

15:39.803 --> 15:41.371
Huge bummer.

15:41.372 --> 15:43.306
So disappointing.

15:45.109 --> 15:46.142
Hey.

15:46.143 --> 15:47.110
Hey.

15:47.111 --> 15:48.044
Are you guys okay?

15:48.045 --> 15:49.245
Huh?
Yeah.

15:49.246 --> 15:51.781
Why wouldn't we be?
Oh, the baby thing.

15:51.782 --> 15:53.249
Oh, yeah, whatever.

15:53.250 --> 15:55.018
Oh, Christmas-themed
movie snack. Nice.

15:55.019 --> 15:57.620
(Chuckles) Don't reach
into the living room!

15:57.621 --> 16:00.390
(Both laugh)

16:00.391 --> 16:02.592
Wow, I-I thought you guys
would be devastated.

16:02.593 --> 16:03.960
Oh.

16:03.961 --> 16:06.362
You know, we're actually
kind of relieved.

16:06.363 --> 16:08.631
We were freaking out for about
a day and a half there.

16:08.632 --> 16:10.900
Yeah, this whole thing
got us thinking.

16:10.901 --> 16:12.902
Maybe we're not ready
for kids yet after all.

16:12.903 --> 16:15.038
Yeah, we were thinking
maybe we would just get a dog.

16:15.039 --> 16:16.105
Get a puppy!

16:16.106 --> 16:17.307
Can you imagine...

16:17.308 --> 16:19.409
That would be the cutest thing!

16:19.410 --> 16:21.144
(Yelling)
No!

16:21.145 --> 16:23.179
Oh. Our movie snack.

16:23.180 --> 16:25.114
Are you kidding me?!

16:25.115 --> 16:27.383
All you ever talk about
is having kids!

16:27.384 --> 16:29.018
And now you have
one little freak-out

16:29.019 --> 16:30.820
and you want to get
a dog instead?!

16:30.821 --> 16:32.355
No. Unacceptable!

16:32.356 --> 16:33.489
You're gonna turn around,

16:33.490 --> 16:35.491
you're gonna go home, get naked,

16:35.492 --> 16:38.294
lie together as man and wife
until Lily is great with child.

16:38.295 --> 16:39.495
Right now!

16:40.197 --> 16:41.764
I'm serious! Go, go, go!

16:44.168 --> 16:46.469
(Singsongy): Marshall and
Lily got in trouble.

16:46.470 --> 16:48.204
And you!
Ooh.

16:48.205 --> 16:50.373
Barney, you look real stupid
in that suit.

16:50.374 --> 16:52.909
You're gonna go get your money
back and give it to charity.

16:52.910 --> 16:55.211
And I don't mean that stripper
you keep e-mailing us about,

16:55.212 --> 16:57.547
even though we beg you
to take us off that list.

16:57.548 --> 17:00.083
I can't give this suit back.

17:00.084 --> 17:01.584
Ted, I glow in the dark.

17:01.585 --> 17:03.553
I finally glow in the dark!

17:03.554 --> 17:06.489
Criminals of New York! Attention!

17:06.490 --> 17:09.224
This man is wearing a
diamond-covered suit!

17:09.226 --> 17:10.226
You could retire

17:10.227 --> 17:11.394
on the pants alone!

17:11.395 --> 17:13.396
Merry Christmas!

17:13.396 --> 17:15.897
(Stuttering)

17:17.667 --> 17:20.203
So, if I get a large popcorn,
you want to go split-skees or...

17:20.204 --> 17:21.537
And you...

17:22.071 --> 17:23.439
You did not move

17:23.440 --> 17:26.442
to the greatest city on earth
to become a coin-flipping bimbo.

17:26.443 --> 17:28.411
So here's how it's gonna work:

17:28.412 --> 17:30.613
Heads, you take the job
at World Wide News;

17:30.614 --> 17:32.682
Tails, you take
the job at World Wide News.

17:32.683 --> 17:34.250
Ow!
(Coin clinks)

17:34.251 --> 17:36.419
Hey, looks like
somebody got a new gig!

17:36.420 --> 17:39.088
Fine, I'll call them tomorrow.

17:39.089 --> 17:41.224
I'll call them right now.
(Annoyed muttering)

17:41.225 --> 17:43.559
(Cell phone ringing)

17:43.560 --> 17:44.560
Hello.

17:44.561 --> 17:45.728
Ted, I can't get married!

17:45.729 --> 17:46.829
Yes, you can! You love her!

17:46.830 --> 17:48.431
You're right, I do! Thanks, Ted!

17:56.774 --> 17:59.242
One for <i>It's a Wonderful Life,</i>
please.

18:01.111 --> 18:03.179
Thank you.

18:05.649 --> 18:07.850
Hi.

18:14.158 --> 18:16.459
We're idiots.

18:16.460 --> 18:18.328
This kid doesn't stand a chance.

18:20.731 --> 18:23.499
We're ready for this.
We're ready for this.

18:25.202 --> 18:27.937
Wow.

18:27.938 --> 18:30.039
That's a lot of zeroes.

18:30.040 --> 18:32.108
Y-you sure you're not
missing a decimal point?

18:32.109 --> 18:33.376
Nope.

18:33.377 --> 18:35.144
And that's the tour.

18:35.145 --> 18:37.847
Uh, staff meeting's at noon,
you'll meet everyone there,

18:37.848 --> 18:39.282
but first you need
to head down to security.

18:39.283 --> 18:41.217
You need to get
your picture taken.

18:41.218 --> 18:42.785
For your I.D. badge.

18:42.786 --> 18:45.688
Oh.

18:47.825 --> 18:49.325
You sure?

18:49.326 --> 18:51.494
Positive.

18:54.798 --> 18:55.865
And there's more.

18:55.866 --> 18:57.433
Do you still do that thing
where you give

18:57.434 --> 18:58.801
people in need
clothes for job interviews?

18:58.802 --> 18:59.702
Yeah. Why?

18:59.703 --> 19:02.638
Bring 'em in, boys!

19:08.178 --> 19:10.747
(Chuckles)

19:10.748 --> 19:12.949
Merry Christmas.

19:12.950 --> 19:15.251
Thank you, son.
Son?!

19:15.252 --> 19:17.353
It's just an expression.
I'm still not your dad.

19:26.864 --> 19:28.264
Congratulations.

19:28.265 --> 19:30.666
You know, that was
really cool what you did.

19:31.235 --> 19:32.201
When we all needed it,

19:32.202 --> 19:33.603
you got us back
on the right path.

19:33.604 --> 19:36.506
It's what I do.

19:36.507 --> 19:38.975
Hey, Ted, if I, um,
if I ever get married

19:38.976 --> 19:40.710
and you're not
the guy I'm marrying...

19:40.711 --> 19:42.111
Big mistake, but go on.

19:42.112 --> 19:44.380
...I could really use
someone like you.

19:44.381 --> 19:46.015
You know, in case I freak out.

19:46.016 --> 19:47.750
<i>When</i> I freak out.

19:47.751 --> 19:48.985
You interested?

19:48.986 --> 19:52.255
Are you asking what I
think you're asking?

19:52.256 --> 19:55.425
Ted, will you be my best man?

19:55.426 --> 19:57.960
Scherbatsky...

19:57.961 --> 19:59.695
I'm gonna crush it.

20:09.436 --> 20:10.470
Hi, there.

20:10.471 --> 20:11.771
We've had a lot of fun tonight,

20:11.772 --> 20:14.140
but on a more serious note,
this is the time of year

20:14.141 --> 20:16.309
when we remember
the importance of giving.

20:16.310 --> 20:20.546
And there's no greater gift
than the gift of booty.

20:20.547 --> 20:25.285
So, this holiday season,
why not bang someone in need?

20:25.286 --> 20:27.987
I'm Barney Stinson,
and that's...

20:27.988 --> 20:29.789
One to grow on.

20:29.790 --> 20:30.957
Um, no.

20:32.559 --> 20:36.494
Hi, there. You know, we've
had a lot of fun tonight...

